headline: Humana Stock Falls on Disappointing Earnings Forecast
summary: Humana’s shares slipped as nervous investors focused on earnings guidance that came in below Wall Street projections.  Humana, an insurer that focuses on the Medicare business, said it was targeting at least $9 in adjusted earnings per share in 2026.  Humana said its guidance was conservative.

headline: UnitedHealth Revenue Outlook Shifts As Margin Focus And Risks Mount
summary: UnitedHealth Group is forecasting its first annual revenue decline in decades for 2026. The company is under increasing regulatory scrutiny related to Medicare Advantage payments. Management is signaling a shift toward prioritizing profit margins over top line growth. For a company of UnitedHealth Group’s scale, a projected revenue decline is a meaningful signal, especially after decades of expansion.
